  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6817 sitting just above the massive negative gamma wall at 6810 (-55.6B), dealers are positioned to buy any dip back toward 6810-6815, creating strong technical support but amplifying volatility in this zone. The breakout regime with -145B total GEX means dealers will mechanically chase momentum - buying rallies toward the 6830 positive gamma flip where they'll switch to selling, and aggressively buying any breaks below current levels. Watch 6810 as the critical fulcrum - a break below triggers cascading dealer buying into the negative gamma stack, while a push above 6820 faces increasing dealer selling pressure toward 6830.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaw action with strong support at 6810 and resistance building toward 6830.",
